Resource Types: Engine, IA Crew/Squad (4-10 person), Hotshot Crew, Prevention

NOTES: Housing available in approximately 20 year old FEMA trailers.  Housing is primarily allocated to fire seasonal employees.  Trailers are triple occupancy and have one private bedroom and one room with two bunk beds.  Rental rates are above average for Forest service duty stations elsewhere in R3.  Bunk beds are not designed for adults and can only comfortably fit individuals up to 5'6.  Rental properties available in Safford and Duncan AZ, approximately 40 minutes to 1 hour one way commute.  Rentals can typically be found in the 600 to 1000/month range.  District housing is not recommended and is in serious disrepair.

Engine crewmembers are housed in a bunkhouse in Duchesne that is shared with employees from other program areas on the district (Range, Recreation, Wildlife etc.)
